2.  Synopsys Commands                                        Command Reference
                             create_track_pattern

NAME
       create_track_pattern
              Creates  a  track  pattern  for specified routing layer and site
              definition.

SYNTAX
       int create_track_pattern
              -layer layer
              [-site site_def]
              [-tech tech]
              [-library library]
              [-type type]
              [-direction direction]
              [-offsets offset_list]
              [-spacing spacing]
              [-spacings spacing_list]
              [-mask_pattern mask_list]
              [-widths width_list]
              [-reserved_for_widths reserved_flag_list]
              [-relative_to core_area|block_boundary]
              [-end_grid_relative_to core_area|block_boundary]
              [-end_grid_low_offset low_offset_list]
              [-end_grid_high_offset high_offset_list]
              [-end_grid_low_steps low_steps_list]
              [-end_grid_high_steps high_steps_list]

   Data Types
       layer                  collection
       site_def               collection
       tech                   collection
       library                collection
       type                   string
       direction              string
       offset_list            list
       spacing                float
       spacing_list           list
       mask_list              list
       width_list             list
       reserved_flag_list     list
       low_offset_list        list
       high_offset_list       list
       low_steps_list         list
       high_steps_list        list

ARGUMENTS
       -layer layer
              Specifies the routing layer based on  which  the  track  pattern
              will  be  created.   You  can use layer name, layer number, or a
              collection containing one layer object.

       -site site_def
              Specifies the site definition based on which the  track  pattern
              will be created.  You can use site definition name, or a collec-
              tion containing one site definition object.  If  not  specified,
              the  default  site definition is used if available, otherwise an
              error is issued.

       -tech tech
              Track pattern will be created in this  technology.   Default  is
              the  current  library's tech.  This option is mutually exclusive
              with the -library option.

       -library library
              Track pattern will be created in the technology of this library.
              Default  is the current library.  This option is mutually exclu-
              sive with the -tech option.

       -type type
              Specifies the type of the track pattern to  be  created.   Valid
              values are uniform and non_uniform.  Default is uniform.

       -direction direction
              Specifies  the  direction  of  the  track pattern to be created.
              Valid values are horizontal and vertical.  Default will use  the
              preferred  routing  direction of the layer.  If there is no pre-
              ferred routing direction, or the preferred routing direction  is
              not horizontal or vertical, then an error is issued.

       -offsets offset_list
              Specifies  the location of each track in the track pattern.  The
              units for the offsets are specified in the technology file; usu-
              ally  it  is  microns.   For creating non_uniform track pattern,
              this option is mandatory.  For creating uniform  track  pattern,
              this option must contain one element if specified.  If not spec-
              ified when creating uniform  track  pattern,  default  will  use
              track_offset  attribute  specified for the layer. If there is no
              track_offset attribute set, then half of  the  spacing  will  be
              used.   In  any  cases, the offset value must be greater than or
              equal to zero, otherwise an error is issued.

       -spacing spacing
              Specifies the pitch distance between each  track  of  the  track
              pattern.   The unit for the spacing is specified in the technol-
              ogy file; usually it is micron.  This option  can  be  specified
              only  when creating uniform track pattern.  Default will use the
              pitch of the layer.  The spacing  value  must  be  greater  than
              zero, otherwise and error is issued.

       -spacings spacing_list
              Specifies  the  pitch  distances between each track of the track
              pattern.  The unit for the spacing is specified in the  technol-
              ogy  file;  usually  it is micron.  This option can be specified
              only when creating uniform track pattern.  This options is mutu-
              ally  exclusive  with  the  -spacing  option.  Each value in the
              option must be greater than zero, otherwise and error is issued.
              If  this  option is specified, then the list size of this option
              must be same as list size of the -offsets option.

       -mask_pattern mask_list
              Specifies the mask pattern for the track pattern to be  created.
              Valid values for the elements of the list are mask_one, mask_two
              and mask_three.  If this option is specified  when  creating  an
              non_uniform  track  pattern,  then  the list size of this option
              must be same as list size of -offsets option.

       -widths width_list
              Specifies the associated wire width for each track of the  track
              pattern.   Tracks  that have width attribute can only be used by
              shapes whose width matches the track's width.  The units for the
              widths  are  specified  in  the  technology  file; usually it is
              microns.  By default, tracks created based on this track pattern
              have  no  width attribute and have no usage constraint.  If this
              option is specified when creating a non_uniform  track  pattern,
              then  the list size of this option must be same as the list size
              of the -offsets option.  If this option is specified when creat-
              ing  an uniform track pattern, then the list size of this option
              must be one.  The width value, when specified, must  be  greater
              than  or  equal  to the minimum width of the layer, otherwise an
              error is issued.

       -reserved_for_widths reserved_flag_list
              Indicates whether the tracks created by this track  pattern  are
              reserved  tracks.  Reserved tracks can only be used by nets with
              a non-default rule.  This option  can  be  specified  only  when
              -widths  option  is specified.  If this option is specified when
              creating a non_uniform track pattern, then the list size of this
              option must be same as the list size of the -offsets option.  If
              this option is specified when creating an uniform track pattern,
              then the list size of this option must be one.

       -relative_to core_area | block_boundary
              Specifies  the  alignment  of  track  line of the track pattern.
              Based on the option, one of the track line will  be  aligned  to
              lower  boundary of core area bounding box or block bounding box.
              Although tracks will be  created  in  complete  block  boundary.
              Default is core_area;

       -end_grid_low_offset low_offset_list
              Specifies  a  list of offset from the left or bottom edge to the
              starting point of the first grid rectangle.  This option  should
              be  specified  together  with  options -end_grid_high_offset and
              -end_grid_low_steps  and  -end_grid_high_steps.  and  they   are
              should in same list size.

       -end_grid_high_offset high_offset_list
              Specifies  a  list of offset from the left or bottom edge to the
              ending point of the first grid rectangle.  This option should be
              specified   together   with   options  -end_grid_low_offset  and
              -end_grid_low_steps  and  -end_grid_high_steps.  and  they   are
              should in same list size.

       -end_grid_low_steps low_steps_list
              Specifies  a  list of steps to use when creating subsequent grid
              points. Each offset in the list is the distance between the pre-
              vious  starting  grid point and the current starting grid point.
              This  option  should  be   specified   together   with   options
              -end_grid_low_offset      and      -end_grid_high_offset     and
              -end_grid_high_steps. and they are should in same list size.

       -end_grid_high_steps high_steps_list
              Specifies a list of steps to use when creating  subsequent  grid
              points. Each offset in the list is the distance between the pre-
              vious ending grid point and the current ending grid point.  This
              option    should    be    specified    together   with   options
              -end_grid_low_offset     and      -end_grid_high_offset      and
              -end_grid_low_steps. and they are should in same list size.

       -end_grid_relative_to core_area | block_boundary
              Specifies  that  subsequent  grid points need to be created with
              respect to core area bounding box or lower left of block  bound-
              ing  box.  This option should be specified together with options
              -end_grid_low_offset.  default is core_area.

DESCRIPTION
       The create_track_pattern command enables you to create a track  pattern
       in the technology of the current or specified library. A technology can
       have at-most one track pattern for a specific site definition and rout-
       ing layer combination.

       You  can  create either an uniform track pattern or a non_uniform track
       pattern.  A uniform track pattern has same spacing between tracks.  The
       -offsets,  -widths and -reserved_for_widths options, if specified, must
       have one element.

       A non_uniform track pattern can have different spacing between  tracks.
       The  -offsets  option  is mandatory for creating non_uniform track pat-
       tern.  The -mask_pattern, -widths and -reserved_for_widths options,  if
       specified, must have same size as -offsets option.

   Multicorner-Multimode Support
       This command has no dependency on scenario-specific information.

EXAMPLES
       The following example creates a non_uniform horizontal track pattern on
       layer M1 for default site  definition  in  the  technology  of  current
       library.   The  track  pattern  has four tracks with specified offsets,
       widths and mask pattern.

         prompt> create_track_pattern -layer M1 -type non_uniform \
            -direction horizontal -offsets { 0.3 0.5 0.7 1.05 } \
            -mask_pattern { mask_one mask_two mask_one mask_two } \
            -widths { 0.15 0.1 0.1 0.1 }
         1

       The following example creates a uniform vertical track pattern on layer
       M2  for site definition unit in the technology of current library.  The
       tracks for this track pattern start from offset 0.3, and has spacing as
       0.2 and width as 0.1. The mask pattern is alternating.

         prompt> create_track_pattern -layer M2 -site unit -type uniform \
            -direction vertical -offsets { 0.3 } -spacing 0.2 \
            -widths { 0.1 } -mask_pattern { mask_one mask_two }
         1

       The  following  example creates a uniform track pattern on layer M3 for
       default site definition using default attributes.

         prompt> create_track_pattern -layer M3
         Warning: '-direction' option not specified. Using preferred routing direction of the layer vertical. (NDMUI-379)
         Warning: '-spacing' option not specified. Using pitch of the layer 0.14. (NDMUI-379)
         Warning: '-offsets' option not specified. Using half spacing 0.07. (NDMUI-379)
         1

SEE ALSO
       remove_track_patterns(2)
       report_track_patterns(2)

